omputer science but with deep interests in physics. I am currently working at Rice University to recover data from partially damaged telescope data using machine learning and developing my ability to solve interdisciplinary problems in both physics and computer science. </p>\n<p>Here's a few technologies I've been working with recently:</p>"}}]},"jobs":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Undergraduate Researcher","company":"Solar Physics Research Group","location":"Houston, TX","range":"August 2019 - Present","url":"http://solar.rice.edu/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Develop machine learning algorithm (Random Forest) to recover damaged data from a telescope</li>\n<li>Verify data recovered using previous data under a similar physical condition</li>\n<li>Ensure the entirety of the data before a new telescope is deployed and make the algorithm applicable to other data recovery job</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Management Intern","company":"Polaris & Dawn Consulting","location":"Beijing, CN","range":"June - August 2019","url":"http://www.polarisanddawn.com/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Developed a course scheduling system using Python (pandas) to accelerate the workflow</li>\n<li>Used Google Map API to develop configured maps to help customers understand different school</li>\n<li>Proposed and implemented the automated scheduling and feedback system between consultants, teachers and clients and saved 10 hours/week of manual work</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Undergraduate Research Assistant","company":"T.W.Bonner Nuclear Laboratory","location":"Houston, TX","range":"May - July 2017","url":"http://bonnerlab.rice.edu/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Used machine learning methods and high energy physics tools like ROOT and TMVA under Linux enviroment analyze particle collision data with C++.</li>\n<li>Collaborated with <a href=\"http://wl33.web.rice.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Prof. Wei Li</a> and more than 3000 collaborators 